r surface number density,\nobtaining a value of the 3D inner power law of\n$\\gamma=1.38\\pm0.06_{sys}\\pm0.01_{stat}$. Conclusions. The MWNSC shares its\nmain properties with other extragalactic NSCs found in spiral galaxies. The\ndifferences in the structure between bright giants and RC stars might be\nrelated to the existence of not completely mixed populations of different ages.\nThis may hint at recent growth of the MWNSC through star formation or cluster\naccretion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Jan 2020 18:04:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-12"}
